headline: Shell Unit Bought Up Nvidia, Apple, and Microsoft Stock
summary: The asset manager of a large oil firm increased positions in large-cap tech stocks.  Shell  Asset Management Co., which manages pension funds for London-based Shell, bought more shares of  Nvidia Apple  and  Microsoft  in the second quarter.  Samco, as the asset manager is known, disclosed the trades, among others, in a form it filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission.
